      "Without the Moon's stabilizing pull, Earth's axial tilt would wobble chaotically.",
      "Permanently shadowed polar craters hold confirmed deposits of water ice.",
      "The Moon has only about one-sixth of Earth's surface gravity.",
      "Moonquakes can ring the Moon like a bell for nearly an hour."
