    "overview": "The Milky Way is the barred spiral galaxy that contains our solar system, a vast pinwheel of an estimated 100 to 400 billion stars spanning roughly 100,000 light-years. Our Sun sits about 26,000 light-years from the centre, in a minor spiral arm, completing one orbit of the galaxy every 225 to 250 million years. From a dark site the galaxy appears as a pale, milky band arching across the night sky, the combined glow of countless distant stars, which is how it earned its name. At its heart lies the supermassive black hole Sagittarius A*.",
